			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				  Okay, this is for all my fellow druids out there.<BR>
<BR>
 In answer to the posts questoning why a 'friend to the animals' class would have such a spell it is quite simple. Druids and Rangers spend the most time around animals and, as a result, know just how to make them flee in panic (or calm themselves) =)<BR>
<BR>
 Now, this spell is a lvl 1 but I found that waiting until 4 or 5 was the best way to go. Once you can take on, depending on your area, giant rats, young lions, pumas then this spell lets you get a few free blasts off with burst of flame/fire before entering melee. Just snare, panic, and blast until the panic wears off. <BR>
 While this spell is good for getting agroed animals off of you during a melee (unwelcomed guests) the animal will flee and most likly bring backup when it returns. I once paniced a Highland lion (to my surprise it didn't resist) and found myself stareing down four lions AND the highland soon after.<BR>
  Use it, practice it, and learn it. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
  Ustke<BR>
  Druid of Brell
				</font>
