			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Two things...<BR>
1. I don't think anyone mentioned the animal you cast this on will return and attack you after the spell wears off.<BR>
<BR>
2. More than once I have cast this spell on a lion in East Commons, usually when my party is busy with an Orc Centurion and the uninvited lion joins in. The paniced animal runs away. I warn the party that the lion will be back. As I watch in the direction the animal fled, not one but two lions come in and attack me.<BR>
<BR>
Here's what I am guessing happened. Any creature that would normally assist the lion in battle is triggered if the lion runs near the creature as the lion flees or as the lion returns. It could have been coincidence so please post if you have any information on this.<BR>
<BR>
Rayfik the Druid
				</font>
